{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"daring-subhedral-pelican","description":"# CI: `cast Verified` casts NO vote when workflow-conclusion aggregation resolves to `skipped` — green CI leaves the change un-landable\n\n## Summary\n\nThe `cast Verified` job in `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` (~lines 442-468) aggregates\nthis run's job conclusions via `im-open/workflow-conclusion@v3.0.0` into `WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION`,\nthen casts the Gerrit `Verified` label from it (`vote-type: ${{ env.WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION }}`,\nsuccess→+1, failure|cancelled→-1). When the aggregation resolves to **`skipped`** — even though\nevery real CI job SUCCEEDED — the cast step aborts with\n`##[error]Unknown vote-type 'skipped': expected clear, success, failure or cancelled` (exit 1),\nso **no `Verified` vote is posted at all**. The change then sits at `Verified = (none)` and is\nun-submittable despite fully-green CI, until a human notices and comments `recheck`. Two defects\ncompound here:\n\n1. **The aggregation can yield `skipped` spuriously.** The workflow's own comment (lines ~444-447)\n   notes `im-open/workflow-conclusion` takes a REST list-jobs *snapshot* that depends on the\n   needed jobs being terminal first; a timing/ordering race can fold a not-yet-finalized job in\n   as `skipped`, producing an overall `WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION=skipped` while the jobs are actually\n   green.\n2. **The cast step is not robust to an unexpected conclusion.** `skipped` (and any value outside\n   `clear|success|failure|cancelled`) hard-errors the job instead of failing safe — so a transient\n   aggregation glitch becomes a **silent no-vote block** (the change looks stuck, not failed),\n   rather than a clear `-1` or an automatic retry.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Push a change to `refs/for/main` whose CI is fully green.\n2. Observe (occasionally) that all CI matrix/optionality/golden-path jobs succeed, but the final\n   `cast Verified` job FAILS with `Unknown vote-type 'skipped'`, and the Gerrit `Verified` label\n   stays unset.\n3. Comment `recheck`; the re-run casts `Verified +1` normally.\n\n**Observed instance:** change 743 (`eclectic-spotted-barb`), GitHub Actions run 29540921742.\nJobs: `CI (ubuntu, py3.11/3.12/3.13)`, `CI (macos, py3.13)`, `golden-path`, all `optionality`,\n`require resolvable rebar ticket` = **success**; only `cast Verified` = **failure**\n(`WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION: skipped`, `VOTE_TYPE: skipped` → exit 1). No `Verified` vote posted.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n\n- **Expected:** green CI casts `Verified +1` deterministically; a transient aggregation hiccup\n  either resolves to the true conclusion or fails in a way that still lands a vote / auto-retries,\n  never leaving a green change silently voteless.\n- **Actual:** an aggregation that resolves to `skipped` aborts the cast job, posting no `Verified`\n  vote; the change is stuck until a manual `recheck`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The `cast Verified` step handles a `skipped`/unexpected `WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION` without\n  leaving the change voteless — e.g. it re-resolves the true conclusion (re-query after all needed\n  jobs are terminal), or maps an unexpected value to a safe, actionable outcome (retry, or a clear\n  `-1` with a diagnostic), never a bare exit-1 that posts nothing.\n  - Proving: a run whose aggregation would resolve `skipped` still results in a posted `Verified`\n    vote (or an explicit retry), verified against `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`.\n- [ ] The aggregation is hardened against the terminal-ordering race (the needed jobs are\n  guaranteed terminal before the snapshot, or the snapshot ignores `skipped` when successes exist),\n  so `WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION` reflects the real conclusion.\n- [ ] A regression guard (workflow unit/lint or a documented manual check) covers the\n  `skipped`-conclusion path.\n\n## Notes\n\nDiscovered while landing the enrich-queue prune race fix (`eclectic-spotted-barb`, change 743):\nall CI green, but `Verified` never posted due to this. Not a defect in that change's code — a\npre-existing CI-orchestration flake. Worked around via `recheck`.","id":"bad2-6dc6-1ed0-449f","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"CI: `cast Verified` casts NO vote when workflow-conclusion aggregation resolves to `skipped` — green CI leaves the change un-landable"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784247006478813001,"uuid":"1d7c32fc-acd0-4c77-8b2e-eda094dfe762"}